parameters: \n< Serena >When should the three of us meet again?

\n< Tim >The basement stairs are hidden. They're originally
used for storing books...

\n< Tim >Bardan-kun changed everything without permission.
He said he would change it back before the manager
comes back...

\n< Tim >I'm done using the bathroom. I don't think I'll
need to use the back room for a while.

events.name: 19-sub6 バーダンとセレナとティム

parameters: ーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーー
19-sub6 バーダンとセレナとティム
ーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーーー

\n< Barden >Hey? If we talk about rumors, there's something-
Oh!

\n< Serena >Lord Tim... It's been a while... Well, we did meet
a few days ago...
\n< Barden >Hey, hey, don't just stand there, come over here.

\n< Barden >Just kidding, just kidding, today is Tim- kun's
birthday-! Yay!
\n< Serena >I haven't heard. Is that so, Lord Tim?
\n< Barden >How old did Tim-kun turn this year?

\n< Tim >I'm not exactly sure. Around 13... maybe.
Probably...
\n< Barden >By the way, I'm 12. Remember that, okay?

\n< Barden >What's wrong? Can't handle it? Come on, let's
celebrate even more!

\n< Serena >Well, I have heard that there are such events
depending on the region.

\n< Serena >In my house, we don't particularly celebrate
individual birthdays.

\n< Serena >Even if I'm told to celebrate, it's troublesome.
What should I do?
\n< Barden >Eh? Well, I've never been celebrated either!

\n< Tim >Ah... I also... don't really do anything special
for my birthday...

\n< Barden >...Looks like we've got three birthday beginners
gathered here...

\n< Barden >Well, anyway, from what I've heard, we're supposed
to eat and drink a lot, and then dance!
\n< Tim >...Ah, well, um, I haven't really danced before...
\n< Tim >S-Sorry, I was watching from here...

\n< Barden >Well then, forget it. Hey Serena, come over here.
You can't dance, can you?
\n< Tim >Barden-san, um... about that, not really...

\n< Tim >And Serena-san, you're pregnant... so you
shouldn't do anything too strenuous...
\n< Serena >......I suppose there's no other choice.

\n< Barden >Alright, alright, ladies, lend me your hands...!
Okay, one, two, one, two!
\n< Serena >Ngh, you, your steps are all messed up...

\n< Barden >Shishishi, I've never really done any proper
dancing either, you know!

\n< Serena >Like this. Place your hands on my waist, and step
right, right, left.

\n< Barden >Shishishi, ohoho, it's quite interesting, isn't
it? Well then, like this, like this!
\n< Serena >Ngh! You fool! Don't bump into my stomach!

\n< Barden >Cecilia? Sorry for bumping into Serena with her
huge belly. There's only so much I can avoid, you
know.

\n< Serena >Ngh! You fool! Consider the difference in our
strides!

\n< Barden >Cecilia? Ah, sorry, sorry. My legs are long, you
see.
\n< Tim >Um, your breathing... it's in sync... or rather...
\n< Barden >Ah, well, we've exercised together many times...
\n< Serena >Ah, ah, it's nothing, Lord Tim.

\n< Tim >Just when I thought you suddenly appeared, it's
your birthday...

\n< Tim >I'm glad I could meet Serena-san, but... I can't
fully enjoy it in this awkward situation...
\n< Tim >I wonder what will happen from now on... me.

\n< Tim >At first, we were supposed to start a postal
service together... and we said it was to earn
money for that... but little by little...

\n< Tim >Poison is absolutely no good. No matter how much
money it makes. Well, actually, is the money
really making a profit?

\n< Tim >You haven't been working for days and you didn't
even show your face...

\n< Tim >I know Bardan-kun's true intentions. He's trying
to please me and cover up the fact that things
aren't going as he planned...

\n< Tim >Well then, isn't today a chance? Serena-san is
here too.

\n< Tim >If I were to tell Bardan-kun that I'm quitting
now... I'm sure Serena-san would support me.
\n< Tim >That's right, I'll say it. I'll say it...

\n< Tim >Open this door and say it right away, Bardan-kun!
I'm quitting!... I mean...

\n< Tim >If I can just say those words, then everything
else will be done on impulse...

\n< Tim >Let's calm down for a moment... Let's rehearse it
in my head one more time...

\n< Tim >It's okay. Even if things get a little weird,
Serena-san will support me.
\n< Tim >This is my only chance. Now, now...

\n< Tim >Did she... go home? Well, forget about Bardan-kun,
but Serena-san wouldn't do something like that...

\n< Tim >Ah, Barden... kun. Welcome back... I was surprised
because both of you weren't here...

\n< Barden >Oh, naughty naughty. We also wanted to go to the
bathroom, you know. We went looking for one
outside.

\n< Barden >I wonder how far Serena went? I think she'll be
back soon.

\n< Barden >Can you stop suddenly speaking informally? It
surprised me.
\n< Serena >I took it! Give it back!

\n< Barden >Hey, why are you standing there like that? Sit
down.

\n< Barden >Oh, really? Then shall we dance? I reviewed it in
my head, so I can do better than earlier, you
know?
\n< Serena >Don't touch me, leave me alone...!
\n< Barden >What's wrong? Why are you suddenly in a bad mood?

\n< Tim >As I thought, you two have a good relationship.
That's really...

\n< Serena >...What part of our conversation made you think
that...?

\n< Serena >I was holding back because it's also a celebration
for Lord Tim.

\n< Serena >At this point, I'll say it clearly. I dislike
shallow people like you.

\n< Tim >......Um, the person you dislike...? Being able to
do such a thing...
\n< Serena >What happened? Are you feeling okay?
\n< Tim >I'm sorry... Is it okay if we call it a day today?
\n< Serena >W-Well, of course that's fine, but...

\n< Tim >Today... today has become a very... very enjoyable
birthday.
\n< Tim >Both of you, really... thank you so much...
\n< Serena >Lord Tim, you seemed strange at the end...

\n< Serena >No, of course. It's Lord Tim's birthday and yet
you're being a burden.
\n< Serena >And on top of that, in the middle of it...

\n< Serena >...I have done something unforgivable. I hope I
can make it up to you someday...
\n< Tim >The plate that had a meat pie on it.

\n< Tim >In the end, Bardan ate it all. It's not a big deal
though...

\n< Tim >It seems like it was done on purpose to make the
store look messy and hide the stairs. I'm not sure
if there's any meaning behind it...

\n< Tim >It seems like it was intentionally made to look
messy inside the store, supposedly to hide the
stairs. I'm not sure if there's any meaning behind
it...

\n< Tim >It seems like it was intentionally made to look
messy inside the store, supposedly to hide the
stairs. I'm not sure if there's any meaning behind
it...

\n< Tim >It seems like it was done on purpose to make the
inside of the store look messy and hide the
stairs. I'm not sure if there's any meaning behind
it...

\n< Tim >It seems like they intentionally made a mess
inside the store and hid the stairs. I'm not sure
if there's any meaning behind it...
